</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="296" pageId="7" pageNumber="294" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[675,1210,1549,1694]" lastBlockId="9.[112,648,215,477]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="296" pageId="7" pageNumber="294">DIAGNOSIS. — Very large species.Fastigium wide, bearing three small ocelli arranged as an equilateral triangle. Inner and outer tympana both oval and very small. Inner subapical spurs of TIII increasing in length through tibia length, the longest almost as long as basitarsus III. FWs present in females (and so certainly in males), but short. Female ovipositor with dorsal valves apex ornamented with transverse crests, ventral valves with ventral teeth. Female genitalia hardly sclerotised, having the shape of a finger; aperture of spermathecal duct trench-like, located apically and ventrally on the papilla. Spermathecal duct short.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
